headline: First Solar Issues Lower-Than-Expected Revenue Outlook for 2026. The Stock Is Falling.
summary: First Solar  was falling 17% in premarket trading Wednesday after issuing downside revenue guidance for the 2026 fiscal year.  The solar panel maker reported fourth-quarter earnings of $4.84 a share, 30 cents below the average analyst estimate as tracked by FactSet.  Coming into the earnings report, First Solar’s stock had declined 6.9% this year but had gained up 55.1% over the past 12 months.

headline: First Solar Stock Falls 13%. What’s Behind the Drop.
summary: First Solar  was down 13% in Wednesday trading after issuing downside revenue guidance for the 2026 fiscal year.  The solar panel maker expects fiscal 2026 revenue in a range of $4.9 billion to $5.2 billion, which is below analysts’ expectations for $6.16 billion, according to FactSet.  The solar panel maker reported fourth-quarter earnings of $4.84 a share, 30 cents below the average analyst estimate as tracked by FactSet.
